The family of the two Amish girls, age 7 and 12, who were abducted by a man and woman on a 'shopping trip' for slaves, are building a garage for the couple who safely returned the girls to their home.

Jeffrey and Pamela Stinson of Bigelow, New York, received the shock of their life on August 14, when the two missing girls, who they recognized from news reports, knocked on their door, about 15 miles from where they disappeared near their family farm stand in Oswegatchie, New York.

Mr Stinson gave the girls, who he said were wet, cold, and still in their traditional Amish attire, some watermelon and juice, and then, after a long discussion with his wife, decided it was better to drive the girls home rather than alert the police. 

